Flask.test_request_context(*args, **kwargs)
    - creates a WSGI environment from the given values (see werkzeug.test.EnvironBuilder)

Flask.request_context(environ)
    - creates a RequestContext() object
    - pushes it at the top of the request contexts stack (flask.request)

    >>> from flask import request
    >>> with app.request_context(environ):
    >>>     do_something_with_request(request)

    >>> from flasks import request
    >>> ctx = app.request_context(environ)
    >>> ctx.push()
    >>> try:
    >>>     do_something_with_request(request)
    >>> finally:
    >>>     ctx.pop()
        

ctx.RequestContext(app, environ, request=None)
    - do not use this class directly, instead use test_request_context()
    or request_context()
    
